title: Rock n' roll the greatest years: 1967 volume 2
brief_description: Relive some of the great hits of the year 1967, including; “Happy Jack” (The Who), “Autumn almanac” (The Kinks), “Zabadak” (Dave Dee Dozy Beaky Mick & Tich), “San Franciscan nights” (Eric Burdon), “Dedicated to the one I love” (Mamas & Papas), “Respect” (Aretha Franklin), “Mellow yellow” (Donovan), “Hole in my shoe” (Traffic), Soothe me” (Sam & Dave), “I can see for miles” (The Who), “I’m a man (The Spencer Davis Group), “The Wind cries Mary” (Jimi Hendrix experience), “Sweet soul music” (Arthur Conley) and “Creek alley” (Mamas & Papas).
